# WordPerfect

**Category:** ventures  
**Domain:** software / word processing  
**Website:** https://www.wordperfect.com (Corel product page)

## Overview
WordPerfect is a word processing application originally developed by Satellite Software International (SSI) in Orem, Utah. First released in 1979 for mainframes and minicomputers, the software gained prominence in the 1980s and 1990s as the dominant word processor for personal computers, particularly in legal, government, and corporate environments. Known for its powerful formatting, keyboard-centric interface, and reveal codes feature, WordPerfect was a key competitor to Microsoft Word and at one point held the largest share of the word processing market.

The company behind the software, renamed WordPerfect Corporation, was acquired by Novell in 1994 and later sold to Corel Corporation in 1996. Corel continues to develop and sell WordPerfect Office, a suite that includes the word processor alongside spreadsheet, presentations, and other productivity tools. Although its market share has declined since the rise of Microsoft Office, WordPerfect maintains a devoted user base in legal and document-intensive professions.

## Utah connection
WordPerfect’s roots are deeply tied to Utah’s tech history. The software was created at Brigham Young University (BYU) and developed through a company headquartered in Orem, Utah. WordPerfect Corporation became one of the state’s first major software success stories, employing thousands of people in Utah Valley during its peak. The company’s growth helped establish the region’s reputation as a hub for software development—a precursor to today’s Silicon Slopes ecosystem. Even after acquisition, some development and support operations remained in Utah for many years.

## Key people
- **Alan Ashton** – Co-founder of WordPerfect Corporation; BYU professor who helped write the original code.
- **Bruce Bastian** – Co-founder of WordPerfect Corporation; provided business leadership and funding.
- **Brent B. Baird** – Early executive who served as CEO during the company’s rapid growth.
- **Pete Peterson** – Long-time president of WordPerfect Corporation.